<title>ITALY: SanPaolo funds Telecom Argentina.</title>
<headline>SanPaolo funds Telecom Argentina.</headline>
<dateline>TURIN, Italy 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Italy's Istituto Bancario San Paolo di Torino has granted financing of $63.7 million or 108 billion lire to Telecom Argentina in order for it to buy equipment from Italy's Italtel, a San Paolo statement said.</p>
<p>Telecom Argentina, the country's second largest phone company, is controlled by Italian state telecoms holding Stet and France Telecom through Nortel Inversora SA. Telecoms systems maker Italtel is controlled by Stet and Germany's Siemens.</p>
<p>The funding is for 11 and a half years and follows a line of credit agreed recently from San Paolo to Telecom Argentina to purchase technology from Italian cable laying company Sirti, whcih is also controlled by Stet.</p>
<p>--Milan bureau +392 66129507</p>
